# 2026-04-04-dream



## D is for dream

I know I said yesterday I wasn't going to keep sniping the A to Z blogs word choice. But dang,
'Dream' is a great one especially when paired with the question of 'What do I dream of'?

I don't dream of a collapse of society, I want a refocus.

Suburbia collapsing from mc mansions into dome houses.
Tool sharing becoming a norm. Wild flowers taking over grass front yards. To see small decentralized food
stores for all. Vegetable exchanges. Small wind farms and less centralized energy grids.

I dream of politics aligning with individuals. Finding the debates raising up to a higher level of sophistication
then the current rhetoric. Maybe people who actually try to change the world for the better getting a chance. Find
a way to push out the dogma of the last hundred years.

I dream of riding an electric bullet train and then taking my off on my bike from whatever forest that vehicle drops me off near.

Id love to see the world brought together by the internet and not see what it was meant to be crushed into capital for a few.

I dream of universal basic income, and a world that has artists and engineers.

People who understand that we all dream, that perspectives don't need to always align but that fundamentally you 'can' disagree respectfully.
That government has a responsibility to help, that it should be an oroborus that enriches all of our lives. Through education, health, social welfare
and justice for all.

Lastly, being ok with childish aspirations in dreams. Because its what, as a child I thought adulthood wuold be.

All of us with our agency, dreaming, making the world into a place we'd all hoped it to be.


